des:
If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : feedback@MeridianLighting.com
Amazon Alexa and the Meridian Lighting home products work together to help you control home appliance easily.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your Meridian Lighting products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our free ""Meridian Lighting"" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register oneMeridian Lighting account in our Meridian Lighting app;
(3). You need to have some Meridian Lighting devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our Meridian Lighting app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in ""Meridian Lighting"" skills;
(5). If you have not already done so, download Amazon ""Alexa"" app from android, ios or Amazon app market site;
(6). Configure Echo with ""Alexa"" app;
(7). Search Meridian Lighting skill from the Alexa app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of Meridian Lighting, and you'll be navigated to Meridian Lighting login page;
(9). Input your Meridian Lighting account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on kitchen light""
“Alexa, turn off kitchen light""
“Alexa, dim living room light""
“Alexa, brighten living room light""
“Alexa, set the living room light to 20 percent""
“Alexa, set bedroom light to Blue""
